<title>BELGIUM: Belgian federal spending eased in Q1 1997.</title>
<headline>Belgian federal spending eased in Q1 1997.</headline>
<dateline>BRUSSELS 1997-04-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>Credits taken up for primary spending by the Belgian federal government eased by an inflation-adjusted 3.1 percent to 347.7 billion francs in the first three months of 1997, the Budget Ministry said in a statement.</p>
<p>In the year earlier period, spending totalled 351.7 billion francs.</p>
<p>The ministry attributed the fall to tight government control over departmental spending.</p>
